Stocks closed solidly higher on Wall Street Tuesday, more than regaining the ground they had lost a day earlier. The S&P 500, the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose and the Nasdaq rose. Small-company stocks rose even more than the rest of the market, a signal that investors were feeling a more optimistic about the economy. On Tuesday:The S&P 500 rose 81.21 points, or 1.8%, to 4,649.23.The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 560.54 points, or 1.6%, to 35,492.70.The Nasdaq rose 360.14 points, or 2.4%, to 15,341.09.The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 63.07 points, or 2.9%, to 2,202.95.For the week:The S&P 500 is up 28.59 points, or 0.6%.The Dow is up 127.26 points, or 0.4%.The Nasdaq is up 171.41 points, or 1.1%.The Russell 2000 is up 29.02 points, or 1.3%.For the year:The S&P 500 is up 893.16 points, or 27.8%.The Dow is up 4,886.22 points, or 16%.The Nasdaq is up 2,452.81 points, or 19%.The Russell 2000 is up 228.09 points, or 11.5%.